data.content:
Here's the minimal program (`Program.cs`):

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

Output: `{"name":"Jane","age":30}`

The key is setting `PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` on `JsonSerializerOptions` — this converts PascalCase properties (`Name`, `Age`) to camelCase (`name`, `age`) during serialization.
